data.name: Blackened Chicken with Garlic Mashed Potatoes
data.quickTastyDescription: Juicy blackened chicken served with creamy garlic mashed potatoes for a delicious comfort meal.
detailedCookingInstructions: Start by boiling the potatoes in salted water until tender, about 15-20 minutes.
While the potatoes are cooking, heat the olive oil in a pan over medium-high heat.
Rub the chicken breasts with blackening seasoning on both sides.
Once the oil is hot, add the chicken and cook for 6-7 minutes on each side, or until cooked through and blackened.
While the chicken is cooking, drain the potatoes and return them to the pot.
Add minced garlic, butter, and milk to the potatoes, then mash until creamy. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Once the chicken is done, let it rest for a few minutes before slicing.
data.detailedName: Juicy Blackened Chicken with Creamy Garlic Mashed Potatoes
